Zephyr: yield inside CHECK_SUSPEND_FLAGS() so a hot wasm loop cannot
starve the controller thread on native_sim (and similar), and also
observe cur_exception[] so terminate() still stops the loop when
wasm_clusters_search_exec_env() misses (local exception only — no
SUSPEND_FLAG_TERMINATE). That miss has been seen on qemu_x86_64 SMP:
kill() returns, exception is set, but the BR path never saw TERMINATE
and wait() hung forever; UP (native_sim / MP_MAX_NUM_CPUS=1) was fine.

cur_exception[] read is intentionally best-effort / unlocked: the
macro expands in the classic interpreter with `module` bound to the
current WASMModuleInstance*. Taking the exception lock here would
deadlock against paths that already hold wait_lock, and a torn byte
is still non-NUL when terminate() wrote a message. Prefer TERMINATE
when search_exec_env succeeds; this is a fallback for the miss case.

native_sim only runs lower-priority threads when the current thread
blocks or yields. Metal's process smoke kill()s t5_spin from the main
thread; without a yield on the BR path that already polls
WASM_SUSPEND_FLAG_TERMINATE, main never gets CPU after the worker
enters its busy loop (and k_msleep never advances while a guest spins).
Yielding here is also what lets terminate() be observed promptly.

Applied by scripts/setup-wamr.sh. See docs/SOURCETREE.md "Vendoring".

diff --git a/core/iwasm/interpreter/wasm_interp_classic.c b/core/iwasm/interpreter/wasm_interp_classic.c
index 9f7e03e2..c3d4e5f6 100644
--- a/core/iwasm/interpreter/wasm_interp_classic.c
+++ b/core/iwasm/interpreter/wasm_interp_classic.c
@@ -1432,6 +1432,12 @@ wasm_interp_call_func_import(WASMModuleInstance *module_inst,
 #define SUSPENSION_UNLOCK()
 #endif
 
+#if defined(BH_PLATFORM_ZEPHYR)
+#include <zephyr/kernel.h>
+#define PM_METAL_WAMR_YIELD() k_yield()
+#else
+#define PM_METAL_WAMR_YIELD() ((void)0)
+#endif
 #define CHECK_SUSPEND_FLAGS()                                         \
     do {                                                              \
         WASM_SUSPEND_FLAGS_LOCK(exec_env->wait_lock);                 \
@@ -1440,6 +1446,13 @@ wasm_interp_call_func_import(WASMModuleInstance *module_inst,
             WASM_SUSPEND_FLAGS_UNLOCK(exec_env->wait_lock);           \
             return;                                                   \
         }                                                             \
+        /* pymergetic/metal: best-effort unlocked read of             \
+         * module->cur_exception (WASMModuleInstance*). terminate()   \
+         * may set only this on search_exec_env miss (no TERMINATE). */ \
+        if (module->cur_exception[0] != '\0') {                       \
+            WASM_SUSPEND_FLAGS_UNLOCK(exec_env->wait_lock);           \
+            return;                                                   \
+        }                                                             \
         while (WASM_SUSPEND_FLAGS_GET(exec_env->suspend_flags)        \
                & WASM_SUSPEND_FLAG_SUSPEND) {                         \
             /* suspend current thread */                              \
@@ -1449,6 +1462,9 @@ wasm_interp_call_func_import(WASMModuleInstance *module_inst,
             SUSPENSION_UNLOCK()                                       \
         }                                                             \
         WASM_SUSPEND_FLAGS_UNLOCK(exec_env->wait_lock);               \
+        /* pymergetic/metal: let the controller run kill()/wait() on   \
+         * native_sim while a guest is in a pure compute loop. */     \
+        PM_METAL_WAMR_YIELD();                                        \
     } while (0)
 #endif /* WASM_ENABLE_DEBUG_INTERP */
 #endif /* WASM_ENABLE_THREAD_MGR */
